name: AnalgesicsForAcutePain
title: Analgesics for Acute Pain
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: All human prescribable analgesic medications used to treat acute pain for patients with a diagnosis of sickle cell disease (SCD) with vaso-occlusive episode (VOE).),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to pain medications.),(Inclusion Criteria: 1.	Opioids
2.	Opioid combinations
3.	Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs)
4.	Other analgesic agents),(Exclusion Criteria: • Analgesic medications not available in the US 
 • Ophthalmic and topical analgesic medication (non-systemic agents)
 • Acetylsalicylic acid  (Aspirin) when not used in combination with an allowable opioid
 • Analgesic medications with a transdermal route of administration)
